From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 00:30:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip-pcie: Restore RK3399 6.1 PHY power-on behavior

The known-good Rock Pi 4 / RK3399 Armbian 6.1 path only took a PCIe PHY
lane out of idle on the first shared PHY power-on.  That lane de-idle
write happened after the shared PHY reset was deasserted and after the
PLL-lock address was selected.

A later upstream change moved the lane de-idle write before the shared
power counter so all four lanes are taken out of idle.  That is a sensible
general fix, but it is not the behavior of the Rock Pi 4 / RK3399
6.1 baseline known to train the PCIe SATA card successfully.

The 6.1 baseline also kept the PHY TEST_WRITE strobe asserted when
"disabling" the write path: PHY_CFG_WR_DISABLE had the same value as
PHY_CFG_WR_ENABLE.  Upstream later fixed that strobe handling, but the
working Rock Pi 4 / RK3399 baseline used the older behavior.

Restore the 6.1 PHY behavior for this compatibility build:

  - return immediately for subsequent shared PHY power-on calls,
  - deassert the shared PHY reset on the first call,
  - select the PLL-lock config address,
  - then take the first lane out of idle,
  - keep the PHY config TEST_WRITE strobe behavior matching 6.1.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c
@@ -24,7 +24,7 @@
 #define PHY_CFG_ADDR_MASK     GENMASK(6, 1)
 #define PHY_CFG_WR_ENABLE     1
-#define PHY_CFG_WR_DISABLE    0
+#define PHY_CFG_WR_DISABLE    1
 #define PHY_CFG_WR_MASK       BIT(0)
 #define PHY_CFG_PLL_LOCK      0x10
 #define PHY_CFG_CLK_TEST      0x10
 #define PHY_CFG_CLK_SCC       0x12
@@ -135,10 +135,6 @@
 
 	guard(mutex)(&rk_phy->pcie_mutex);
 
-	regmap_write(rk_phy->reg_base, rk_phy->phy_data->pcie_laneoff,
-		     FIELD_PREP_WM16(PHY_LANE_IDLE_MASK,
-				     !PHY_LANE_IDLE_OFF) << inst->index);
-
 	if (rk_phy->pwr_cnt++) {
 		return 0;
 	}
@@ -153,6 +149,10 @@
 	regmap_write(rk_phy->reg_base, rk_phy->phy_data->pcie_conf,
 		     FIELD_PREP_WM16(PHY_CFG_ADDR_MASK, PHY_CFG_PLL_LOCK));
 
+	regmap_write(rk_phy->reg_base, rk_phy->phy_data->pcie_laneoff,
+		     FIELD_PREP_WM16(PHY_LANE_IDLE_MASK,
+				     !PHY_LANE_IDLE_OFF) << inst->index);
+
 	/*
 	 * No documented timeout value for phy operation below,
 	 * so we make it large enough here. And we use loop-break
